headline: Lamb Weston Earnings Beat Sparks Questions On Fries Demand And Margins
summary: Lamb Weston Holdings (NYSE:LW) reported quarterly earnings and revenue that were ahead of expectations. The company paired this performance with more cautious guidance, including softer signals on future demand and margin outlook. Investor reaction was negative, with concerns focused on structural profitability and demand trends in core frozen potato products. Analysts are split, with some highlighting operational execution and others emphasizing the uncertainty around future growth and...
